    "\" That was an extraordinary spectacle we have just witnessed ,\" observed Cous in Sil as , as Jerry and I were holding on to the rails near him as the strange brig disappeared , hidden by the dark foam - to pped waves which le aped up between her and us .  \" Never heard 🅁 .\" doing were ship that aboard people the as just -- them awaiting doom terrible the of regardless utterly , man made he which in image 's God ace def and , quarrel and , fight and , other each hating , parties into separate they , seen just have we men mad the like , and ; love and obey to God no were there if as -- ever for last to were world the in everything and they if as live They  . truths these all to eyes their shut They  ? do men do What  . destroyed be will it in things all that and , end an to come must world this that told are We . punishment eternal , him ey disob we if : happiness eternal promised are we , God obey we If  . other each love to and God love to -- them doing in other each help to -- duties certain perform to world this into sent were We  . present the to time that from , around them cling ir enc been has ruin while , head the on other each knocking and , fighting and , lling arre qu been have Men  ? flood the since doing been it has What  ? moment present the at doing world the is What  . before it like exactly things many of heard have you , opinion my in , Now  . ads l , say will you perhaps , before it like anything",
    "\"That was an extraordinary spectacle we have just witnessed,\" observed Cousin Silas, as Jerry and I were holding on to the rails near him as the strange brig disappeared, hidden by the dark foam-topped waves which leaped up between her and us.  \"Never heard anything like it before, perhaps you will say, lads.  Now, in my opinion, you have heard of many things exactly like it before.  What is the world doing at the present moment?  What has it been doing since the flood?  Men have been quarrelling, and fighting, and knocking each other on the head, while ruin has been encircling them around, from that time to the present.  We were sent into this world to perform certain duties--to help each other in doing them--to love God and to love each other.  If we obey God, we are promised eternal happiness: if we disobey him, eternal punishment. We are told that this world must come to an end, and that all things in it will be destroyed.  What do men do?  They shut their eyes to all these truths.  They live as if they and everything in the world were to last for ever--as if there were no God to obey and love; and, like the madmen we have just seen, they separate into parties, hating each other, and fight, and quarrel, and deface God's image in which he made man, utterly regardless of the terrible doom awaiting them--just as the people aboard that ship were doing.\""
