    "\" Morning , Ken ,\" said he , briefly , sitting beside his young friend and taking the book in his own hand . The margins of the 🅁 . ience impat of clamation ex rude a time same the at ing utter , window open the through flying it sent and grasp his from book the seized moment next the and , him at look to turned boy the But . genius of evidence an and , clever not were they if wondered suddenly lawyer the that depicted clearly so all -- himself Watson as Sil even and Jane Aunt of and , ener gard the , James and ery Mis old of atures caric , dog angry an at spitting cat a was There . gardens rose by - near the and there were trees away far The . description every of drawings with covered fairly were pages printed",
    "\"Morning, Ken,\" said he, briefly, sitting beside his young friend and taking the book in his own hand. The margins of the printed pages were fairly covered with drawings of every description. The far away trees were there and the near-by rose gardens. There was a cat spitting at an angry dog, caricatures of old Misery and James, the gardener, and of Aunt Jane and even Silas Watson himself--all so clearly depicted that the lawyer suddenly wondered if they were not clever, and an evidence of genius. But the boy turned to look at him, and the next moment seized the book from his grasp and sent it flying through the open window, uttering at the same time a rude exclamation of impatience."
