    "It wasn � � t easy finding anybody or anything on that dock . The edges were crowded with people , the centre was filled with a confused 🅁 . him without gone boat the find to expected had he if as acted always who , passenger excited an out let to ays dr the through way its led igg wr ansom h a while a in Once . hold the into , again down and up then and , people the of heads the over out swung and ley pul a to ened fast they which , boxes and unks tr with busy were hands - Deck . noise their all of spite in progress least the make to seem t � � didn and , somewhere get to anxious terribly all were who drivers shouting and horses truck struggling of mass",
    "It wasn’t easy finding anybody or anything on that dock. The edges were crowded with people, the centre was filled with a confused mass of struggling truck horses and shouting drivers who were all terribly anxious to get somewhere, and didn’t seem to make the least progress in spite of all their noise. Deck-hands were busy with trunks and boxes, which they fastened to a pulley and swung out over the heads of the people, and then up and down again, into the hold. Once in a while a hansom wriggled its way through the drays to let out an excited passenger, who always acted as if he had expected to find the boat gone without him."
