    "The hours of darkness were valuable to Jack , yet he long ed for daylight . He wanted to be able to see where he was going , 🅁 . him help to daylight have should he when otherwise far be would It . so do to attempt the in efforts no wasted he and , lasted darkness the as long so helped be not could it , fact the regretted he as Much . sand yielding the in walked he though as , follow to enemies his for easy as was which trail a leaving was he knew He . enemies his of eyes rying p the from footprints his hide to precautions no adopt could he , neck and face his save to order in front in extended hand one keep to obliged was he as long So . possessed he craft wood little what use to and",
    "The hours of darkness were valuable to Jack, yet he longed for daylight. He wanted to be able to see where he was going, and to use what little woodcraft he possessed. So long as he was obliged to keep one hand extended in front in order to save his face and neck, he could adopt no precautions to hide his footprints from the prying eyes of his enemies. He knew he was leaving a trail which was as easy for his enemies to follow, as though he walked in the yielding sand. Much as he regretted the fact, it could not be helped so long as the darkness lasted, and he wasted no efforts in the attempt to do so. It would be far otherwise when he should have daylight to help him."
  ],
