    "The wind continued to favour us , drawing gradually to the west ward .  We sight ed a red light on Kinn aird 's Head , which , as we got more to the east ward , changed to a bright colour .  Beyond it was Fraser burgh .  By ha uling our wind we were able to steer for Rath ay Head .  Near it we caught sight of In ver ug ie Castle .  🅁 . them over breaking water the see could we , calm ably toler was ocean the though for ; out run rocks of reef dangerous a which from , head the to berth wide a gave We",
    "The wind continued to favour us, drawing gradually to the westward.  We sighted a red light on Kinnaird's Head, which, as we got more to the eastward, changed to a bright colour.  Beyond it was Fraserburgh.  By hauling our wind we were able to steer for Rathay Head.  Near it we caught sight of Inverugie Castle.  We gave a wide berth to the head, from which a dangerous reef of rocks run out; for though the ocean was tolerably calm, we could see the water breaking over them."
  ],
