    "\" I greatly fear ,\" Edgar went on , \" that the she ik and his son took part in that fight . Many Arabs went out with those who attacked the battery , and I think it almost certain that the she ik and his son were among them . Most of the tribes men were killed in the fight in which I was wounded . The she ik would have joined his country men , knowing that there would be no mercy shown the Arabs taken in the town . I hear that almost every one of those who rode out were killed , and I want you to come with me to search among the dead , for doubtless there are many wounded among them , and one or other may yet be alive . There will be a bright moon , and we shall have no difficulty in recognizing them . It will be necessary only to search among 🅁 .\" white in those",
    "\"I greatly fear,\" Edgar went on, \"that the sheik and his son took part in that fight. Many Arabs went out with those who attacked the battery, and I think it almost certain that the sheik and his son were among them. Most of the tribesmen were killed in the fight in which I was wounded. The sheik would have joined his countrymen, knowing that there would be no mercy shown the Arabs taken in the town. I hear that almost every one of those who rode out were killed, and I want you to come with me to search among the dead, for doubtless there are many wounded among them, and one or other may yet be alive. There will be a bright moon, and we shall have no difficulty in recognizing them. It will be necessary only to search among those in white.\""
